SQL Command Categories Summary

Category	                      Purpose        	                                                              Main Commands                                  Examples
DDL       	Defines and modifies the structure of databaseobjects like tables, schemas, or views.	     CREATE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE, RENAME	         CREATE TABLE Employees (...);
DML       	Used to insert, modify, or delete data in existing tables.                                	INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE	                       INSERT INTO Employees VALUES (1, 'John', 'HR', 50000);
DQL	        Used to query (fetch/retrieve) data from the database.	                                       SELECT	                                     SELECT * FROM Employees WHERE Department='IT';
DCL    	 	  Controls user access and permissions on database objects.	                                     GRANT, REVOKE	                                GRANT SELECT ON Employees TO John;
TCL	      	Manages transactions to maintain data consistency and integrity.	                         COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT, SET TRANSACTION     	COMMIT;, ROLLBACK;

üß† Quick Understanding
Type           	What It Does	                           Affects
DDL	          Defines database structure              Database schema
DML          	Manipulates data	                      Table data
DQL	          Retrieves data	                        Table data (read-only)
DCL	         Manages access control	                  Users & permissions
TCL	         Controls data transactions	              Session & transaction level

üîπ Simple Example Flow
-- 1Ô∏è‚É£ DDL: Create table
CREATE TABLE Employees (
    EmpID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    EmpName VARCHAR(50),
    Department VARCHAR(30),
    Salary DECIMAL(10,2)
);

-- 2Ô∏è‚É£ DML: Insert data
INSERT INTO Employees VALUES (1, 'Alice', 'IT', 70000);

-- 3Ô∏è‚É£ DQL: Retrieve data
SELECT * FROM Employees;

-- 4Ô∏è‚É£ TCL: Control transaction
COMMIT;

-- 5Ô∏è‚É£ DCL: Grant permissions
GRANT SELECT ON Employees TO John;

üîπ Mnemonic to Remember:

üí° ‚ÄúD-D-D-T-D‚Äù ‚Üí DDL, DML, DQL, TCL, DCL
Think of it as:
Define ‚Üí Manipulate ‚Üí Query ‚Üí Transact ‚Üí Control

‚úÖ In short:

Category	Focus	Key Idea
DDL	Structure	Defines the database
DML	Data	Adds or changes data
DQL	Query	Reads data
TCL	Transaction	Saves or undoes changes
DCL	Control	Manages user permissions
